description.narrative: 1. Hazardous and Suspected Hazardous Areas assigned by the Lebanese Mine Action Center are released in accordance with National Standards to the benefit of the affected community. 2. Risks of landmines and Explosive Remnants of War-related accidents for women, men, girls, and boys from host communities and refugee populations living nearby contaminated areas are reduced through Risk Education. 3. Social inclusion and economic reintegration of victims of landmines and Explosive Remnants of War-related accidents and their families is supported. 4. Accountability and technical capacities of Lebanese Humanitarian Mine Action stakeholders are reinforced.
"Enhanced resiliance of vulnerable groups through Improved access to resources, livelhoods and socioeconomic reconstruction"
